data.description: This charming downtown bungalow near Patty Jewett golf course offers a blend of comfort and modern amenities. The interior features Oak hardwood flooring and a barrel wood-burning stove, creating a warm, inviting atmosphere with ample natural light. The kitchen, recently upgraded, includes Quartz countertops, new cabinets, a gas 5-burner cooktop, convection double ovens, LVP flooring, and a farm-style sink, combining style with functionality. The primary suite boasts a walk-in closet and an updated bathroom.  2 Additional bedrooms and full bath that has been updated.  Outdoors, the property showcases a stucco exterior with a private backyard perfect for hosting gatherings. Unwind by the 1100-gallon koi pond/waterfall that runs year around, enjoy barbecues under the covered patio. The front yard is easy to maintain, equipped with an auto sprinkler system, enhancing the home’s curb appeal. Recent updates include siding, paint, and gutters (2022). The oversized two-car detached garage, heated and with separate power including a 220 plug, serves as an ideal workshop. Additional features of this eco-friendly home include active solar panels, a newer HVAC system with A/C and humidifier (under warranty), an updated electrical panel with an external 220 plug, and triple-pane, double-hung windows with a lifetime warranty. The attic is insulated with R77 material for energy efficiency. The property comes with a washer and dryer and is secured with a North fence double-hung car gate, an ally 7' gate, and 3 man gates. There's an ongoing roof claim with SAFECO for upcoming maintenance, including solar panel servicing.
